  "prompt": "How do chickens make their eggs?",
  "response": "Chickens produce eggs through a complex process involving their reproductive system:\n\n1. Ovary development:\n- Female chickens have an ovary containing thousands of potential egg yolks\n- One yolk is released into the oviduct each day\n\n2. Egg formation stages:\n- Yolk is released and travels through the oviduct\n- Egg white (albumen) is added around the yolk\n- Egg membranes form\n- The shell is created in the shell gland, using calcium carbonate\n- The shell hardens and is coated with a protective layer\n\n3. Egg laying:\n- The fully formed egg travels to the cloaca\n- The chicken then pushes the egg out through the vent\n\n4. Factors affecting egg production:\n- Age of the hen\n- Breed\n- Nutrition\n- Daylight hours\n- Overall health\n\nMost hens begin laying eggs around 4-6 months old and can produce approximately 250-300 eggs per year.",
